    "faq": {
      "type": "brand-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is Einhell Power X-Change and how does it work?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>Power X-Change</strong> is Einhell's universal 18V lithium-ion battery platform. One battery fits every cordless tool in the Einhell range \u2014 over 350 products including power tools, garden equipment and workshop machines. Buy a battery and charger once, then add bare tools as you need them. For higher-demand tools like lawn mowers, two 18V batteries combine to deliver 36V output.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Are all Einhell Power X-Change batteries compatible with every tool?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. All Power X-Change 18V batteries are compatible with every cordless tool in the Einhell range. Higher-capacity batteries (4.0Ah, 5.2Ah) will deliver longer runtime but all batteries physically fit and power every PXC tool. For 36V tools, you simply insert two 18V batteries.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What warranty do Einhell products come with?",
            "answer": "<p>Einhell products come with a standard warranty, which can be <strong>extended to 3 years</strong> by registering your product online within 30 days of purchase on the Einhell website. Power X-Change batteries can also be registered separately for extended warranty coverage. As an official Einhell stockist, Invicta Tools can assist with all warranty queries.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does Einhell compare to premium brands like DeWalt or Makita?",
            "answer": "<p>Einhell occupies a different position in the market. While premium brands target heavy daily professional use, Einhell delivers <strong>reliable performance at a significantly lower price point</strong> \u2014 making it ideal for contractors who need capable tools across multiple applications without the premium cost. The Power X-Change platform also offers one of the widest compatible tool ranges of any battery system on the market.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is Einhell suitable for trade use?",
            "answer": "<p>Einhell tools are increasingly used by tradespeople who want a cost-effective cordless solution \u2014 particularly for secondary tool kits, site backup tools, garden and landscaping work, and renovation projects. The Power X-Change platform means you can build a comprehensive kit across <strong>power tools and garden equipment</strong> on a single battery system without the outlay of premium brands.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you offer trade pricing on Einhell?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. We offer <strong>competitive trade pricing</strong> across the full Einhell range including Power X-Change bare tools, kits and batteries. Contact our trade team on <strong>01843 593 440</strong> or email <strong>sales@invictatools.co.uk</strong> for volume discounts and trade account enquiries. Free next-day delivery on all orders over \u00a399.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
